EntityDef.description:
This PmGroup defines measurement types within the OverloadProtection_ApOlpPriority area. The AP OLP Priority is set based on the best ARP level for attached UE and is stored in the UE EMM Context. The SGSN-MME uses an AP OLP Priority of 16 for unattached UE. However, both attached and unattached UE can qualify for a specific OLP Priority by indicating one of the following RRC Establishment causes in an Initial UE message sent over the S1-MME Interface:;
* Emergency - OLP Priority based on local Emergency configuration in the SGSN-MME;
* High Priority Access - OLP Priority based on local MPS configuration in the SGSN-MME;
* Delay Tolerant Access - OLP Priority 17;

This measurement provides a tool monitoring issues in the communication between SGSN-MME and MSC over the SGs interface.

This counter is incremented for the following cases:;

* SGSN-MME needs to send an SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST message to the MSC but cannot due to missing TA-LA mapping configuration.;

* SGSN-MME needs to send an SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST message to the MSC but cannot due to no LAI can be selected although there are mapped LAIs to the TAI.;

* SGSN-MME does not receive a response from the MSC to a SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST message.;

* SGSN-MME receives an SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REJECT with any cause code from the MSC.;

Action to be taken if the measurement exceeds its supervised threshold:

Check the EBM log, and look for L_ATTACH or L_TAU events containing a Sub-Cause Code. Continue with the action proposed for the Sub-Cause Code. The Sub-Cause Code reveals if the problem is missing TA-LA mapping configuration, or no mapped LA can be used due to being restricted by access restriction or LA selection profile, or missing response from the MSC, or reject from the MSC (including the cause code given by the MSC). The EBM log also reveals which TA(s), LA(s), and MSC(s) the problem is related to.
It may happen that this counter is incremented but nothing is visible in the EBM log. This happens in case MSC pool is deployed and Location Update fails towards the MSC initially selected but succeeds after fallback to another MSC in the pool. In this case capture the SGs traffic with ITC and search for SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REJECT or no response to SGsAP-LOCATION-UPDATE-REQUEST.

This measurement provides the number of failed Intra-#SGSN# #SRNS# Relocation procedures and intra-#SGSN#/#MME# #IRAT# handover procedures from #LTE# access to #UMTS# access. The counter is incremented when the SGSN receives an Intra-#SGSN# #SRNS# "Relocation Required" message from the source RNC and the relocation procedure fails to continue due to internal reasons or when the SGSN receives a "Relocation Request Acknowledge" message from the target RNC but some of the needed RABs failed to set up.
The internal reasons include the following:
*The srns_relocation feature is deactivated.;
*The #MOCN#-related or Roaming Restriction related configuration does not allow the #SRNS# to the target #RA#.;
*The #SPC# is not configured for the target #RNC#.;
*No #RAB# exists between the source #RNC# and the #SGSN-MME#, or the #PDP# Context is not in stable status.;
*The #SGSN-MME# fails to set up the Iu connection to the target #RNC#.;

This measurement provides the number of returned UEs with GBR bearers retained by the MME. The return of UEs is triggered by service requests, TAU requests, Context Requests, or SGSN Context Requests. 
The measurement covers UEs returned in the following scenarios: 
*The UEs return to the network with retained GBR bearers before the S1TimerGbrBearerDeactivation timer expires.; 
*The S1TimerGbrBearerDeactivation timer is cancelled by paging, and the UEs return to the network with retained GBR bearers within the time specified by the S1TimerGbrBearerDeactivation timer.;
